# This file declares the exact Neuro-Cybernetic Protocol (NCP) pins for Galadriel.
# NCP consumer tools find this file without repository-specific logic.
# The relevant tools are check-consumer-pins.sh and repin-ncp.sh.
# Galadriel pins an immutable release commit instead of a movable tag.
# Each revision row also records the consumer release label.
# The NCP repinner derives the commit from the canonical local tag.
#
# These revision rows need NCP consumer tooling at commit
# 205384508d619923e05aef192bedaeb57cf665fc or later.
# The pinned v0.8.0 runtime checker predates these row types.
# That checker can skip both rows.
# The Galadriel feature graph gate rejects an invalid local descriptor.
# Invalid descriptors are empty, unknown, legacy, partial, or drifted.
#
# The default command-line interface (CLI) graph has no NCP dependency.
# The galadriel-ncp workspace crate has a direct ncp-core dependency.
# The galadriel-eval workspace crate depends on galadriel-ncp.
# The off-by-default CLI `ncp` feature selects the adapter.
# The `ncp-live` feature also enables ncp-zenoh, Zenoh, and Tokio.
cargo_rev       Cargo.toml v0.8.0 2f5bd586d4bb20c90362bb6f5698b7f64057ba4e
cargo_lock_rev  Cargo.lock v0.8.0 2f5bd586d4bb20c90362bb6f5698b7f64057ba4e
